WIP: Playing around with some local galaxy 3D starmap viz ideas

This one's a little busy, but I've always liked the Homeworld-style aesthetic of flat rings indicating the location of the z-plane.

#RStats #rayrender #dataviz https://t.co/ObwMASBoTT

Expand the radius by a factor of 10 and you end up with less of a map and more of a cloud. 200 light years is 0.2% of the diameter of the Milky Way galaxy. All our radio transmissions are well under that 200 ly radius.

It's a big galaxy out there. #RStats #rayrender #dataviz https://t.co/jBR6j46HYG
